cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new method for feature selection that takes into account interactions among features. This is a common problem in machine learning and data science, which suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories. 

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category is the most likely because the paper proposes a new method for feature selection that improves the accuracy of numerical models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category is also likely because the paper proposes a new algorithm for feature evaluation that could be used in various AI applications. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): This sub-category is likely because the paper proposes a new method for evaluating feature subsets, which could be seen as a data structure problem. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): This sub-category is likely because the paper proposes a new method for feature selection that could be applied to image and video data. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): This sub-category is less likely but still possible because the paper proposes a new method for feature selection that could be used in neural networks and evolutionary algorithms.
